It's not something that you did.

00:16:33.039 --> 00:16:35.479
It's something that the render plot function did.

00:16:35.479 --> 00:16:39.679
So we should be able to collapse that down, just say bundle it up to render plot.

00:16:39.679 --> 00:16:41.599
I don't care how it works.

00:16:41.599 --> 00:16:44.280
Just gloss over that for me.

00:16:44.280 --> 00:16:46.479
This would also help for things like modules.

00:16:46.479 --> 00:16:50.320
If you know your module is solid, you could collapse it down to a single group and then

00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:54.359
we'd be good to go.

00:16:54.359 --> 00:16:57.520
Also I'd like to remove objects from the React Log graph.

00:16:57.520 --> 00:17:01.619
